snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a capitalist.

I believe people who build Companies to a certain scale should have the option to pay $0 taxes if that tax amount is reinvested into their business to improve efficiency, infrastructure, people, etc... not dividends to shareholders.

The tax base grows proportionately to investment back within the business that makes it more competitive on a Global scale and the average working woman/man is rewarded for efforts put in.

Making a profit and doing right by the people who put in the work should be in divisible.

I'm a social liberal and financial conservative- we need leadership that meets in the middle and provides solutions for all.

We need a rebalancing of our priorities. The entrepreneur and innovator's should be celebrated and reap the rewards of their efforts. The average working person should be able to afford a life void of financial insecurity- what they do with their income is their responsibility.

When the vast majority of the populace is 1 pay cheque away from financial ruin- we have a problem.
